        public void zoom(double[] dataIn,
                 int xIn,
                 int yIn,
                 int widthIn,
                 int heightIn,
                 int strideIn,
                 double[] dataOut,
                 int xOut,
                 int yOut,
                 int widthOut,
                 int heightOut,
                 int strideOut)
        Zoom region
        Parameters:
        dataIn - The source data.
        xIn - Starting x in the source data.
        yIn - Starting y in the source data.
        widthIn - How wide the region to interpolate is.
        heightIn - How high the region to interpolate is.
        strideIn - How wide the source data is. That is, we may zoom a 10x10 region into a 30x30 image.
        dataOut - The destination array.
        xOut - Starting x in the destination data.
        yOut - Starting y in the destination data.
        widthOut - How wide the region to write into is.
        heightOut - How high the region to write into is.
        strideOut - How wide the destination data is.
